# Feature: Postman Collection

## User Story

As an evaluator,
I want to test the client API easily,
so that I can validate all functionalities without manual setup.

---

## Tasks

### 1. Create Postman Collection File

File:

postman/ms-client.postman_collection.json

---

### 2. Include Endpoints

#### Create Client

POST /clients

Body example:
{
"name": "Juan Perez",
"gender": "M",
"age": 30,
"identification": "1234567890",
"address": "Calle 1",
"phone": "3001234567",
"status": true
}

---

#### Get Clients

GET /clients

---

#### Get Client by ID

GET /clients/{id}

---

#### Update Client

PUT /clients/{id}

---

#### Delete Client

DELETE /clients/{id}

---

### 3. Environment Variables

Define:

- base_url = http://localhost:8080

---

## Rules

- Use clear naming for requests
- Use environment variables
- Avoid hardcoded URLs

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- Collection imports successfully
- All endpoints can be tested
